title: Conspiracy
description: Det. Sgt. Vickers believes that Sen. Det. Banner's personal feelings may have impaired his judgment when Banner makes an all out effort to nail Eddie Parrish, a former policeman who has used his police know-how to muscle in on various rackets.

title: The Soldiers
description: Yarra Central police battle a crime wave of thuggery, hold-ups and the theft of $20,000 worth of goods by a mystery gang. Investigations reveal the culprits as 'The Soldiers', a re-united former teenage gang whose members have just finished serving jail terms. Sen. Det. Banner's pregnant wife, Joy, dies during premature child-birth brought on after being terrorized by a member of the gang.

title: Once a Cop
description: Yarra Central police are confronted with a series of reports about a bad detective. Their investigations lead to an impostor, a former policeman, who is blackmailing a solid citizen caught in an office secretary trap, belting people around with unrestrained sadism, and leading two romantic lives.

title: The Big Spender
description: 19-year old Kay Dixon is attracted by the glamorous life of big-spending racketeer Max Foley, who tries to set up a floating cabaret. Kay finds herself in the ugly world of prostitution, exploitation and violence with no apparent way out. Police investigate Foley when a criminal associate of his is bashed.

title: Night Out
description: Three salesmen from a country town decide on a night out after attending a Melbourne convention. For two of the three, the night turns into disaster when they become involved with a truck driver who is the apparent victim of a robbery and two girls who 'roll' unsuspecting males.

title: The Sunday Mother
description: A little Italian girl is missing. While investigating her disappearance, Yarra Central police discover a kidnapping, a burglary, an alcoholic mother, and an attempted suicide.

title: Not Valentine's Day
description: A city night club serves as a front for vice and crime. As Yarra Central police investigate a number of seemingly unrelated matters, they uncover alarming facts about one of the district's most respected citizens.

title: It's a Great Day
description: Celebrating st. Patrick's Day with rather more enthusiasm than caution, the O'Connell family decides to start its own crime wave in the district, resulting in a sequence of events Which cause a lot of hard work for the Yarra Central police.

title: The Swinger
description: Pop singer John Noble, whose popularity has slumped, is to proud to take ordinary work. When he starts chasing easy money to maintain his lifestyle he becomes involved with drugs and crime - and the police of Yarra Central.

title: The Puritan
description: A deserted wife, Irene Kemp, successfully raises her daughter Thea by running a sly grog house, but when she becomes involved in a robbery and blackmail the whole structure of her life is threatened.

title: Big Brother
description: An expert safe cracker comes out of prison to find his young brother eager to follow in his footsteps. These two, plus a shifty billiards-room proprietor with o fondness for stolen property pose problems for Sen. Det. Banner.

title: The Angry Man
description: A con-man is troubling the police of Yarra Central, but when the search for him begins, Sen. Det. Banner cannot foresee the serious consequences for an old man and his daughter.

title: Information for an Offence
description: Det. Sgt. Vicker's son Jamie becomes caught in the activities of some demonstrators who attack a policeman. Jamie is innocent of complicity, but he is unwilling to inform about the offenders to his father. Jamie finds himself in a difficult position - between Vickers and his son lie the years that separate the generations and brought new attitudes and values. A group of car thieves operating in the area complicates matters for the police, in particular for Det. Peters.

title: A Mugs Game
description: A little girl fails to arrive at school one morning, a factory worker lies about his reasons for being late for work, and the Yarra Central police probe a case which may end in murder.

title: The Legend
description: A down-and-out ex-cricketer, whose days of glory are long gone, is given the opportunity to mace a come back. Police are concerned when his son is connected to a pornography racket.

title: Not at Home
description: An Hungarian architect finds himself working as a quarry laborer after settling in Australia. An argument with his foreman sparks off a crisis in his life and a major emergency for the police of Yarra Central.

title: The Takings
description: A neglected child is taken from a woman involved with a payroll bandits. Their attempt to steal a firm's payroll uncovers a secret held by an employee of the company.

title: The Protest
description: Yarra Central police are faced with unexpected obstacles when they investigate a fatal hit-and-run accident.

title: A Stitch in Time
description: A merchant seaman jumps ship and becomes the only witness to a 'smash-and-grab' raid. Because of personal problems he refuses to identify the criminals, who then carry out other violent crimes.

title: Janie and Janie
description: Investigating an apparently routine case of child neglect, WPC Margaret Stewart stumbles into the nightmare world of schizophrenic Janie Mitchell. Every ounce of Margaret's training, human understanding and bravery is called upon in her desperate struggle to save the life of a baby that Janie has abducted.

title: The Threat
description: A released prisoner with a violent criminal record has two scores to settle - one with his unfaithful wife and the other with Sen. Det. Banner.

title: Take Over
description: An interstate gang launches a campaign of terror in an attempt to takeover local crime. Kenny Kent, a professional burglar, stands up to them alone, and in so doing he unwittingly gives the police their chance to smash the gang.

title: The Girlfriend
description: When detectives first come across the mysterious Faith Cameron, they suspect she is a call girl, then it seems she could be passing a dud cheque. But what is she really up to? Police then link Faith to a jewel thief who switched a paste reproduction for an expensive ring before crashing his getaway car.

title: First Offender
description: The death of a call girl helps Police in the investigation of a robbery apparently committed by the trusted employee of a finance company.

title: We'll Get Him One Day
description: Lesley Fisher is a hardened criminal who specializes in planing robberies, and has returned to Melbourne from Adelaide with a respectable front - wife, a home and good clothes. With his two accomplices he plans a robbery - being careful not to be involved in its execution. He escapes capture by informing on his two henchmen, and detectives fail to find any hard evidence against the shrewd gang leader.

title: By the Book
description: Nature had not dealt kindly with little Willie. In his stunted body, half the size of normal men, is packed all the emotions of others about him. The strange affection that grows between Willie and a woman criminal leads him to the half-world of robbery, violence and eventually his own death

title: It's a Man's Life
description: When Dave Smyth leaves the wharves to join the police force, his father accuses him of becoming a 'lackey of the capitalist classes'. Dave's loyalties are soon put to the test, and the resulting conflict brings trouble for himself and his colleagues at Yarra Central.

title: Plumage
description: The wayward son of a wealthy man is told that he will have to make his own way in the world. He responds by going into business - as a thief. Executing a warehouse robbery, he seems to have been successful until he has to dispose of the goods.

title: The Victim
description: Policewoman Margaret Stewart tries to help a young woman who is emotionally disturbed as a result of being criminally assaulted by a prowler, and has received no understanding from her boyfriend.

title: The Price
description: Ricky Peel escapes from jail and, with the help of some criminal associates, threatens a private detective. Sen. Det. Banner is reunited with a girl he once loved who has just returned to Melbourne.

title: Farewell Little Chicago
description: A man who has publicly criticized the Yarra Central Police is charged with an offense. He then alleges that one of the Detectives has bribed a key witness in the case.

title: Decoy
description: SGT. Macleod is offered a well paid job back in Scotland. He is considering the offer when Vickers asks him to stand in for a bank manager in a police trap for a group of vicious bank robbers.

title: It's the Little Things
description: Vic Tomasetti loves his Downs Sindrome Daughter Lisa, a girl totally misunderstood by her stepmother and others. Her testimony about the shooting of a policeman is not believed due to the contrary evidence given by adults.

title: The Losers
description: Rod Irving has just been released from prison, and is confronted by Ike Vaughan the man that put him there. Rod wants to go straight but Vaughan tries to involve him in crime, and has already caused his wife Bella to become a drug addict.

title: The Comedian
description: Vince Perry thinks his jokes are funny, but he cannot see that they often cause a great deal of trouble and distress. Yarra Central Police are not amused when they find he has returned to the area.

title: The Colonel's Boy
description: Tim Gardner has had all the advantages in life with rich parents. But he has chosen a life of crime. His young wife, Meg does not suspect him but things soon get complicated when a former accomplice targets Gardners operations.

title: The Web
description: An assault between two girls on a street leads to the Yarra Central police unraveling a tangled web when a middle-aged businessman becomes involved with a girl younger than his own daughter.

title: Social Climber
description: Two young baby-sitters throw a party in a rich client's home. They strike trouble, but in doing so they give the Yarra Central police a new line of inquiry into a puzzling series of jewel thefts.

title: Cocktails at 10.15
description: Master criminal Lesley Fisher becomes involved in a vicious underworld vendetta. Police investigations lead to a surprising result.

title: Hush-a-bye
description: Ray Hubbard is studying to get through university, but when his girlfriend becomes pregnant the only solution seems to be an abortion. When things don't go as planned, the Yarra Central police find themselves investigating a con-man, a robbery and a back yard abortionist.

title: Cash and Carry
description: Two men and a woman comprise a gang of thieves stealing cash from the retailers in the fruit and vegetable trade. Yarra Central police find their investigations made difficult by changes in tactics of the gang responsible.

title: The Crush
description: A night club comedian faces personal crisis when his broken marriage catches up with him after 14 years in the shape of his 18 -year-old-daughter. Yarra Central police help sort it out while investigating a call-girl racket and a large liquor theft.

title: Where's Lefty?
description: Some attitudes towards aboriginals are re-evaluated when 'Lefty' Cooper, an Aboriginal contender for the lightweight boxing championship, becomes the target for a crooked bookmaker who stands to lose a great deal of money if 'Lefty' wins the fight.

title: Mr. Fifty Percent
description: The Yarra Central police are faced with an outbreak of well-planned thefts with no recovery of the stolen goods. Third-rate thieves commit skillful offenses under the instructions of a master-mind of unknown identity, referred to as 'Mr. Fifty Percent'.

title: The Great Bank Robbery
description: A confidence trickster tells the Yarra Central police that a young English migrant is planning a bank rubbery. The plight of an old elderly lady complicates the situation.

title: The Word of a Lady
description: Doreen Walsh, wife of a former detective, claims that she has been attacked and raped by three men. During investigations, Sen. Det. Banner and Det. Sgt. Vickers uncover an unusual story.

title: Fizz
description: Herb Doherty, who has a string of minor convictions to his name and is known as a trouble-maker, witnesses a smash-and-grab raid. He also falls in love with policewoman Margaret Stewart.

title: La Truffa
description: A cruel swindle is played on the local Italian community, and police investigation impacts on a domestic crisis with Sgt. Vickers and his student son Jamie.

title: A Good Man Gone
description: Yarra Central police launch an intensive search when Constable Kevin Dwyer disappears while pursuing a car following a series of baffling robberies.

title: The Desecration
description: During an investigation into the violent and apparently senseless desecration of a Catholic Church, Yarra Central police track down a young man who has become embittered towards religion, mainly as a result of a 'fire and brimstone' indoctrinations as a child, they are assisted on the case by highly unconventional priest.

title: Mother's Image
description: Mrs Maguire is a successful business woman and charity worker. However a street accident leads to a complex investigation into the truth about Mrs. Maguire and her daughter.

title: The Unwanted
description: While investigating three assaults on a young girl, Yarra Central police are faced with several other problems, including the disappearance of a small-time criminal wanted for questioning and the defiant old lady.

title: The Marvels of Reproduction
description: Alf Clark and his pregnant wife Jill are in partnership with her idealistic brother in a counterfeiting racket. Problems occur when they become involved with petty criminal Ted Jamieson.

title: A Bit of Culture
description: A local art festival uncovers a raft of problems for the police of Yarra Central. At the center of the trouble is Arthur Deakin - a poet, an alcoholic and a house breaker.

title: Johnny Reb
description: A man becomes rebellious when questioned about his driving, taking a stand on principle against what he sees as an injustice. The Yarra Central police become the center of attention when newspapers get hold of the story and run with it.

title: The Tangled Web
description: Investigations into a series of safe breaking's uncover an unexpected romantic but illegal entanglement when police discover a man with two wives.

title: The Big Bloke
description: Yarra Central police contend with a bank hold-up and a bizarre confidence trick involving the freezing of dead bodies. Suspicion for both crimes centers on the much loved son of a family.

title: My Mate Death
description: While serving a short sentence for theft, young and impressionable Malcolm Tanner formed a hero-worshiping friendship with his tough, ruthless cell-mate Ernie Callan. After serving his sentence, Tanner is overjoyed when Callan offers to come and live with Tanner and his family while continuing his life of crime. However, joy turns to tragedy when it is learned that the the police are hunting his mate, not only because of his criminal activities but because he is a carrier of a deadly strain of smallpox.

title: Free the Queen
description: Yarra Central police face a crime following a 20-year-old pattern. Investigations lead them to master criminal 'chalky' Gunnerson, who is a clever chess player and plans his moves against the police with care and precision. Also involved are his daughters Vivienne and a rather brash young apprentice, Ricky Bevan.

title: The Emerging Man
description: John Anderson, a neurotic young camera enthusiast, unwittingly becomes a key figure in a police search for a couple of jewel Thieves.

title: The Handicapper
description: Yarra Central police investigate threatening letters and attempts to injure a leading professional jockey.

title: Closed Doors
description: A young girl, Tina Findlay, is caught shoplifting, and policewoman Margaret Stewart probes her background to find a reason why. Trying to help Tina proves difficult and unrewarding when she becomes mixed-up with hardened criminals.

title: Message Intercepted
description: Yarra Central police, Who rely heavily on radio communication with D-24, face problems when two criminals steal a police radio.

title: There Goes Betty Seymour
description: An American migrant woman who is homesick has a breakdown and becomes dangerously violent. The plight of her family is worsened when the son becomes involved in a series of service station robberies.

title: The Prisoner
description: While on holidays, Det. Peters gets married in rather rushed circumstances - he was tricked into the marriage by a pregnancy claim. Then, when a prisoner dies in the Yarra Central lock-up, Det. Peters goes through the most trying experience of his life when he is held directly responsible.

title: Brother Animal
description: Feelings of hatred and fear run high in the Yarra Central district when a number of young children are molested by an unknown man. Policewoman Margaret Stewart receives her promotion to Senior Constable.

title: A Key to Paradise
description: Persistence by Const. Dwyer in checking details following a minor car accident leads the Yarra Central police on to the trail of one of the world's most notorious international robberies.

title: A Special Occasion
description: While investigating a series of daring robberies Yarra Central police are confronted with some surprising characters - a pop singer; a hotel manager; two very 'quaint' furniture dealers; and a swinging, headstrong glamor girl.

title: Mad Monaghan
description: Sen. Det. Banner and the Yarra Central police face death when they investigate a seemingly minor complaint about the behavior of Les Monaghan, who is living in a fantasy world in which he sees himself as a soldier hero.

title: The Man from Lightning Ridge
description: Ex-criminal Sam Breen returns to Melbourne with a small fortune in opals that he mined at Lightning Ridge. When the opals are stolen he sets out after the two thieves, intent on obtaining his own justice.

title: Payroll
description: Yarra Central police receive a series of false tips about a planned city payroll robbery, while also dealing with Hayden Beck, an ex-racing car driver with a chip on his shoulder. When a payroll robbery is actually committed, it soon becomes apparent that Beck had been recruited to drive the getaway car.

title: A Gathering of the Clan
description: Police keep watch on a group of criminals planning a daring and unusual robbery - but they disappear when the robbery is imminent. WPC Stewart gets little help investigating a quack doctor who is treating the girlfriend of one of the criminals.

title: Elizabeth the Third
description: Daniel Castle, a timid Englishman, leaves his domineering wife Elizabeth and the shop they own in London, taking money from their joint bank account. Elizabeth pursues him to Australia and discovers he has lost most of the money to two con-men.

title: Smiler
description: Bob 'Smiler' Suttle is a 40-year-old policeman and is still a constable. His resentment leaves him open to a bribery attempt when a criminal tempts him with a scheme that could help him gain a promotion.

title: Wednesday's a Quiet Night
description: A husband and wife's drunken brawl, Banner's search for a man who mutilated a prostitute, and a young boy who wanders into Yarra Central make this Wednesday anything but the usual quiet night.

title: For Better, for Worse
description: Yarra Central police contend with a professional burglar operating in their district who is proving to be most elusive. Constable Kevin Dwyer marries his girlfriend Kay Hogan.

title: The Recruit
description: Constable George Bell, an enthusiastic new recruit, tests the patience of his colleagues with his habit of rushing into things without thinking.

title: Three Man Trick
description: Policewoman Stewart tries to apprehend a bag-snatcher and is helped by a man who identifies himself as Larry Webster, an American FBI agent. He is later exposed as a confidence trickster.

title: Drop Out
description: A vicious assault on a prostitute leads Yarra Central detectives into an investigation of prostitution in the district, and to a mysterious Mr. Frost who is not what he seems.

title: Thought I'd Met Them All, I
description: A young man comes into conflict with his Church when he falls in love with a progressive young girl. His life becomes more complicated when he comes under suspicion for a number of house break-ins.

title: Separation
description: A young girl and her separated parents become the victims when an overbearing mother-in-law takes their affairs into her own hands and hires a private detective.

title: Running Sheet
description: Yarra Central police have to deal with a mysterious shop breaker and a lonely widower. Det. Peters police duties are affected by events in his private life when his marriage is on the rocks.

title: A Trip to the City
description: A man who has always lived in the bush visits the city and takes strong exception to the vice he considers is prevalent in city life. His subsequent actions unleash a campaign of terror.

title: Pratfall
description: Will 'Duff-Duff' Duffy, a clown who specializes in trick falls, and Hugo Smith, a criminal with a child-like personality, have never met, but their stories become intertwined when Yarra Central police investigate a robbery, a suicide and extortion.

title: Point of View
description: An investigation into homosexual activity in Yarra Central leads to the discovery of a number of unusual burglaries.

title: Jailbird
description: Police investigate a payroll robbery with some very unusual features that almost has them stumped.

title: Dark Afternoon
description: A young country girl tries to set herself up as a prostitute in the city. She falls prey to a vice operator who sets up 'Witchcraft' sessions for his clients.

title: The Luck of the Irish
description: Police at Yarra Central become involved in a robbery and an illicit stills racket, and all their investigations take them to the notorious O'Connell family.

title: One thing at a Time
description: While dealing with a teenage shoplifter, Policewoman Stewart experiences a frightening ordeal when they are held hostage by a dangerous escapee from a mental institution.

title: Stream of Conscience
description: A woman's anti-pollution campaign against a manufacturing company helps to uncover theft and corruption within the firm.

title: Everyone Loves a Prang
description: Yarra Central police investigate a feud between rival tow-truck services Which threatens to erupt into violence.

title: As the Crow Flies
description: A tough stand-over group runs a prostitution racket utilizing drugs and abduction. WPC Margaret Stewart finds herself in difficulties while undercover posing as a prostitute to crush the racket.

title: The Monkey Chased the Weasel
description: Lisa Clark, a Doctor's wife, becomes an addict after her husband introduces her to drugs. Investigating a house breaking, police find that a youth , like too many of his age, has become trapped on a road of no return through drug usage.

title: Command Performance
description: A young constable is savagely attacked and seriously injured by five youths. The Yarra Central police put on a 'command performance' act to extract the truth from the suspects?

title: Visitors from Hong Kong
description: Investigations into the theft of valuable but difficult to unload electronic equipment result in Yarra Central detectives investigating a highly organized betting syndicate.

title: So, It's a Living
description: Con-man Jimmy Harrison and his girlfriend turn to burglary, which spells disaster for his two young accomplices and an elderly fence.

title: The Infiltrator
description: When the driver of an interstate gang is arrested, Yarra Central police see their chance to smash the racket by having Det. Peters acting undercover as his replacement.

title: Big Man, Little Man
description: Two men of short stature - one a notorious criminal who exploits his own build to his own advantage, the other a young misfit who resents his size - cause trouble for the Yarra Central police.

title: Could You Speak a Little Louder?
description: When radio talk-back announcer John Drew draws attention to a gang of car thieves operating in Yarra Central, his wife is threatened.

title: False Alarm
description: While police investigate a series of armed robberies, a young accountant tries to help his wife by giving police wrong information and is eventually blackmailed.

title: The Return of John Kelso
description: Yarra Central detectives investigate a brutal assault after John Kelso, a convicted murderer serving a life sentence, is paroled after 25 years.

title: Who Needs Enemies?
description: Blind barrister Jessica Reynolds is persecuted by an unknown intruder.

title: The I.O.U.
description: An escaped convict goes into hiding in Yarra Central, holding a young girl hostage.

title: Who Cares?
description: The adult son of a very influential man goes missing. Can the detectives of Division 4 solve the case before time runs out. Or is all not as it seems

title: They Walk at Night
description: Yarra Central police face a difficult task when the victim of a vicious assault is reluctant to give information against a gang of predators.

title: Bang Bang, You're Dead
description: A bomb explodes in Yarra Central. Suspicion narrows down to a maniac who has escaped from jail, a thief, and a layabout protester. All have reason to seek revenge against the police - especially Det. Banner.

title: Be Good Sweet Maid
description: A young university student reports to police that she has been raped. A young man is charged, then additional information and the probing by the man's defense counsel creates droughts as to the truth of her story. Policewoman Margaret Stewart finds a romantic interest in the police doctor, Robert Whitfield.

title: No Short Cuts
description: An overworked detective, Barry Maguire, is transferred to Yarra Central on temporary duty and tries too hard to convict a criminal, with disastrous results.

title: Now, One with the Bride
description: A young man's bucks party is raided when the best man introduces a pornographic film to the festivities. When Yarra Central police investigate they uncover a world of vice and blackmail.

title: Run for Cover
description: Leo Morrison escapes from prison to prevent his girlfriend marrying someone else, but his plans undergo a change when he picks up a girl hitch-hiker with decidedly unusual views.

title: Handsome Harry
description: Police investigate an attempted murder complaint and discover that a middle-aged veterinary surgeon has bigamous and had married several woman.

title: One Small Step
description: A shop break-in interrupted by Const. Dwyer leads to a serious family altercation involving the police.

title: Live Bait
description: Divison 4 realize they are in the middle of a crime wave when one of the female officers is attacked. They discover this was not an isolated incident but part of a much wider series of crimes against women. And one of Division 4s own may have to pay the ultimate price to apprehend the criminal

title: The War Is Over
description: Division 4 becomes involved when a woman receives threatening letters from her ex husband. As the team instigates they realize there is more to the situation than they thought.

title: Jelly Fingers
description: The detectives of Division 4 are called in to investigate the theft of gelignite from a local mining company. The team works through the usual suspects but it seems a new player may be in town.

title: There Goes the Neighbourhood
description: Attacks on women in a Yarra Central street upset neighborhood relations, and the prime suspect is a man recently released from psychiatric care. Kevin Dwyer receives his long-awaited promotion to First Constable.

title: The Last of the Independents
description: A family of criminals discover that Arthur Mitchell mints his own coins to supplement his pension. To muscle in on the racket, they kidnap his wife to force his co-operation.

title: Grub Stake
description: Two amiable swindlers cause Yarra Central police chaos with a series of clever con tricks.

title: Bent Law
description: Det. Peters is having some personal problems due to his impending divorce, and the Yarra Central police have to investigate an allegation that he is being bribed.

title: You Couldn't Meet a Nicer Bloke Than Dennis When He's Sober
description: Det. Peters, concerned about his divorce, decides to resign from the force. He then meets up with Denis Marshall, an alcoholic whose own marriage is threatened. Peters tries to help Denis, and discovers his own domestic situation is not as bad as he thought.

title: Small Fry
description: Carol Hayes is prepared to break the law in order to keep 7-year-old Ronnie whom she has been caring for. The child belongs to the Turners, and Jean Turner wants him back because her husband Mike is being released from jail.

title: You Can't Trust Anyone
description: A series of expert safe breaking's leads the Yarra Central detectives into an industrial espionage plot.

title: Collision
description: Sgt. Scotty Macleod is looking forward to Christmas until he encounters a drunk-driving accident for Which he feels partly to blame.

title: The Clean Skins
description: While investigating the background of a young man involved in a car crash, Det. Banner comes across clues indicating that he was involved in an illegal racket.

title: No Hard Feelings
description: Const. George Bell returns to Yarra Central for another spell of temporary duty, and once again his enthusiasm and eagerness turns the station upside down.

title: A Continental Gentleman
description: A European paymaster is implicated in a payroll robbery, with tragic results. The Yarra Central police find that prejudice against immigrants in the district can affect their investigations.

title: Once Bitten
description: Jim O'Obrien is released on parole after serving 18 months of a long jail term. His homecoming is marred by treachery and a faithless wife.

title: Pigs Is Pigs
description: Constable Dwyer attempts to establish a youth club for delinquent kids, and becomes involved with the theft of some power tools, a cop with a chip on his shoulder and a tough old matriarch named Porky.

title: The Man Who Dug His Own Grave
description: Police informer Sammy Goodall finds his life is threatened by criminal associates in the Melbourne underworld.

title: To Bribe or Twist
description: The local newspaper and the Yarra Central police become involved when a wealthy woman, the wife of a successful business man, steals jewelery from a shop.

title: The Warder
description: A prison officer is reported missing. He is later found unconscious but unharmed, and police investigate a possible case of revenge or blackmail by ex-prisoners.

title: Man's Only a Battler
description: Constable Dwyer orders Barry Ward, a young owner-driver, to have his truck made roadworthy within five days, but when Barry finds he cannot pay for the repairs he is drawn into crime.

title: Plain Rosy
description: Yarra Central police investigate some burglaries and come to a surprising result. The case involves a plain-looking girl and a heartless petty criminal.

title: Dad
description: Yarra Central police are searching for Sally Young, a prisoner from Fairlea Woman's Prison, who has escaped from policewoman Stewart. An aggressive old man who lives near the police station knows more than he has told them.

title: A Place of My Own
description: Evie Morris is a housewife who turns to prostitution to provide a better home for her family.

title: Rogues Gallery
description: A series of baffling robberies from art galleries plague the Yarra Central police. Matters become complicated when it is revealed there is more than one group responsible.

title: I'm Going to Smash Something Every Day
description: Yarra Central police have a hard time trying to find Neville, a mentally disturbed youth who smashes things when people upset him.

title: You Think You've Got Troubles
description: Yarra Central police have their hands full when an Italian ex-safe breaker if forced back int crime.

title: Finders, Keepers
description: Yarra Central police make a concerted effort to find several unknown people who have picked up packages containing a highly dangerous chemicals.

title: Butcher, Baker, Troublemaker
description: A drunken group of elderly men get together for a surf life-saving club reunion. The party goes sour when one of the old men suddenly drops dead. Rather than report it to the police they decide to bury their friend in the backyard.

title: Herbie
description: Herbie Pike is a balding, middle-aged company clerk who has lived his life by the clock with only dreams of making a lot of money. Suddenly he breaks into crime in a very big way.

title: You Can't Win Them All
description: When Det. Sgt. Vicker's niece comes to visit, Det. Peters takes her out and on one of these occasions his car is stolen. Meanwhile, Yarra Central police are kept busy with a series of vicious assaults and robberies.

title: The Electro Static Organ Revitaliser
description: Sgt. Macleod's wife becomes involved with a woman who has invented a machine which supposedly cures physical illnesses.

title: A Nice Safe Job
description: When top safe-cracker Barney 'Houdini' Ward gets out of Pentridge, his brother Clyde enlists his help to rob $100,000 in diamonds. Barney soon finds there is more to this 'nice safe job' than he was led to believe, and he implements a clever scheme to thwart a criminal organization led by a vicious Goldfinger-type woman.

title: A Waste of Time
description: An habitual criminal, thinking that his son will help him reform, asks Sen. Det. Banner for help in locating him.

title: All Women Are Liars
description: Yarra Central police are faced with a series of crimes committed against women. Their investigations lead to a man who had been undergoing psychiatric treatment and whose wife divorced him, and who is seeking retribution against other women who have divorced their husbands.

title: Cry of Vengeance
description: When an army conscript returns home on leave to find his fiancée bashed and raped, it appears that his drunken brother could somehow be involved.

title: Only a Twenty-Two
description: Armed hold-ups, housebreaking's, a domestic dispute and illegal use of guns cause Yarra Central police to experience a bad weekend with firearms.

title: Come the Revolution
description: An idealistic Scottish locksmith, who has been a communist all his life, resorts to crime when he becomes involved with Cliff Wood, an habitual criminal, to raise funds to go to Moscow.

title: For the Love of Money
description: During a series of housebreaking's, a bank manager is bashed when his home is broken into and his bank keys are stolen.

title: One More War
description: Yarra Central police run into difficulties when they try to solve a number of hold-ups in which the getaway car is driven by a clever, mysterious driver.

title: Birds of a Feather
description: Yarra Central police investigate the actions of a visiting yachtsman, Tom Anderson, who is involved in bird smuggling. Anderson has conned a young girl, Karen, into the smuggling racket, and events culminate with Anderson seeking revenge against Banner.

title: Andrew Shannon
description: Constable Dwyer heads for major trouble when he becomes involved in what appears to be a minor accident.

title: Hide and Seek
description: Det. Sgt. Vickers is set off on a relentless search for counterfeit plates when he learns the name of a man booked for a minor traffic offense.

title: Natural Victim
description: Peter Watson, a previous sex offender recently released from prison, is the suspect when a number of rapes occur in Yarra Central.

title: When in Rome
description: Yarra Central police are confronted with an imported method of committing petty crimes involving the skillful riding of motor cycles.

title: A Bad Lot
description: Yarra Central police move into action when Vickers' wife is terrorized by a youth who loathes the police and is seeking revenge.

title: The Oracle
description: The investigation of an obscenity charge against an underground newspaper, 'The Oracle', leads the police to a subculture of revolution and drugs.

title: Room for Danger
description: Banner gambles with death when he must deal with a man intending to shoot his aged father and then himself.

title: A Trap for Young Players
description: A shopkeeper shoots an intruder and Yarra Central police uncover some facts that cast doubt upon his version of events.

title: Flight Plan
description: Investigations into the theft of a large sum of money from a shipping company involve Yarra Central police in a widespread search which finally leads to Sydney but finds the culprits difficult to track down.

title: Come Play with Me
description: Through a maze of violence and subterfuge, Yarra Central police try to track down the young wife of a wealthy American business man who is reported missing in Melbourne.

title: Take Over
description: An old man demanding to live in a decaying mansion, a factory robbery and the theft of a safe lead to Yarra Central police uncovering a conspiracy.

title: Empty Hand
description: Banner blames himself when a rent collector is shot and robbed. A policeman is used as a decoy in an attempt to trap those responsible, and Det. Peters suffers a serious injury.

title: Afraid of the Dark
description: A tip-off for a planned factory break-in and a domestic dispute that leads to murder confront Det. Dave Edwards, who is assigned to Yarra Central for temporary duty while Det. Peters is in convalescence.

title: Keep Running
description: It's a search for someone who just doesn't want to be found, even for his own good - when a destitute criminal steals some groceries that Yarra Central police suspect contain poisoned food.

title: Simon Says
description: Yarra Central police investigate abusive and threatening phone calls which lead to an apparent terror campaign against a lonely housewife.

title: A Few Hours of Freedom
description: A criminal escapes from the custody of Det. Sgt. Banner in order to find his unmarried pregnant daughter, and Banner becomes personally involved in tracking them down.

title: Two Pot Screamer
description: Circumstances and clues left cause Banner to fear that two ex-burglars he has helped in the past have returned to crime.

title: Travelling Man
description: Det. Peters returns to duty at Yarra Central. When a girl is discovered missing it seems probable that her disappearance is connected with the activities of a cat burglar.

title: Senior Stewart
description: A vicious assault on a small baby alarms the Yarra Central police. They are in for another shock when they learn that policewoman Margaret Stewart is planning to leave the force.

title: The Monkey Game
description: An important case arises at Yarra Central, but Det. Peters is absent under suspicious circumstances, and the uniform branch suspect he is 'moonlighting'.

title: Big Bad John
description: A Sydney policeman, Det. Sgt. John Smith who is known for his rough tactics, causes trouble for Police when he comes to Melbourne in search of his daughter.

title: An Honest Sale
description: Det. Peters becomes involved with a girl whom it transpires is mixed-up in prostitution and robbery.

title: Today Is Eagle Day
description: Sgt. Scotty Macleod is off-duty at the rates office paying a bill when a hold-up gang comes in. Taken hostage and driven to the Mornington Peninsula, Scotty is shot and seriously wounded, and the 'Angel Of Mercy' helicopter is utilized to take him to hospital.

title: The Manner to Which
description: A youth trying to help his mother financially becomes involved with a young criminal, and they both cause the serious injury of a security guard.

title: Three Mouths to Feed
description: Jean Marshall is a young mother of two girls who has left her abusive husband and moved to the city, and needlessly lies to get government welfare assistance. She witnesses a crime, but is reluctant to come forward and give evidence.

title: Once a Crim
description: Banner's judgment is put to the test when a criminal he believes is reformed is connected with a stolen jewelery racket, and his granddaughter and another girl are involved in robberies with violence.

title: The Last Bet
description: Yarra Central police grow anxious when some house break-in's erupt into violence, and all is not as it seems with one of the victims.

title: Life at the Bottom
description: The attempts by a man living on the breadline to unlawfully augment his income, particularly as he is about to loose his job and his wife is expecting a baby, bring him under the scrutiny of the Yarra Central police.

title: A Wild Wild Rose
description: Policewoman Margaret Stewart becomes involved with a teenage girl whose grandmother lays a charge of assault against her. A series of possibly related housebreaking's complicate the investigation which nearly ends in murder.

title: The Grasshopper
description: Yarra Central police investigate a commune when a young courier fails to deliver the drugs he has been sent to buy for a pusher. He mysteriously disappears and is later found dead.

title: The Ninth Life
description: A cat burglar who has lost his nerve marries an ex-prostitute, and together they try to start a new life. However, the wife overhears a former boyfriend planning a $75,000 jewelery store robbery and she is kidnapped by a gang of violent criminals. The Yarra Central police investigate, but the cat burglar decides to take the law into his own hands.

title: A Matter of Survival
description: An outbreak of petty theft, the release of a seasoned criminal, and an underworld vendetta lead police through a maze of inquiries and violence.

title: Isabella
description: A man captures a burglar in his house, but the burglar turns the tables on him and escapes. A neighbor who witnesses the confrontation phones the police. The victim is co-operative and appears to be a good, reliable witness, but he has something to hide, and the burglar has accidentally discovered what it is that could cause his downfall.

title: Voice of the Gun
description: Two escapees, a seasoned criminal and a gun happy youth, commit a vicious murder. Banner is forced into a professional and personal confrontation, facing the torturous question of when is a policeman justified in risking a fatal shot to stop a criminal. In searching his conscience, Banner re-evaluates his own life in the four years since his wife's death, in which he has buried himself in his work. At this time he is re-acquainted with Jenny Franklin, a girl he knew when they were kids. She has returned from overseas to take over her father's homestead, and as they get back together and pick up the threads a deep attachment grows between them.

title: Sweet Kid, Good Family
description: A young electrician just through his apprenticeship is forced by two criminals, who have threatened his pregnant girlfriend, to use his knowledge of alarm systems to help them break into a factory.

title: Inside Information
description: Police are puzzled when a group of criminals blackmail an insurance executive to gain access to confidential information about various properties. They use this and a special camera for a successful series of robberies.

title: The Toffee Apple Man
description: Policewoman Margaret Stewart finds herself in a puzzling situation involving a street vendor. His knowledge of the activities of a criminal gang is something that they are most anxious to keep secret.

title: Too Late for Tears
description: A bank night safe is blown and a man is injured. His young pregnant wife goes missing and Yarra Central police fear for her life.

title: You Never Forget the First Time
description: A series of bushings occur in Yarra Central, and a man once convicted of rape returns to the area to see his daughter, and is almost driven to suicide because of her non-acceptance of him.

title: A Cry of Fear
description: John Porter turns violent after being involved in an accident Which results in brain damage. He attacks several people, including his wife, his neighbor, a barman, and the police.

title: Rules of the Game
description: Banner suspects Rory Collins, a criminal who honors his own set of 'rules', for an attempted robbery of a warehouse. When a policeman is bashed suspicion falls on Collins, but Banner is not convinced and evidence soon emerges that an interstate gang could be responsible.

title: Blood Brothers
description: A young boy with family problems turns to his mate, who is involved in crime, for solace. A notorious Sydney criminal coerces them to become involved in more serious crime.

title: And Pigs Can Fly
description: Det. Sgt. Banner becomes personally involved when the daughter of one of his old friends is involved in a bank robbery with her lover and his brother.

title: Petty Cash
description: Yarra Central police suspect that a lot more than petty cash has been stolen when a finance company safe is blown up.

title: Dear John
description: A safe breaker causes security guard John Walsh to loose his job, then recruits him into crime. When pressure from his criminal associates and trouble with his broken marriage get the better of him, they build into a tragic climax.

title: Waste Ground
description: Yarra Central police are puzzled when they find the body of an old derelict at the scene of a car crash. Their investigations uncover the violence that killed him.

title: The Lock
description: James McQueen is known as 'The Lock', a criminal whose fame in the underworld is almost legendary because of his skill and knowledge with safe combinations and key patterns. 'The Lock' is sprung from prison by a gang led by his son Wayne in order to pull a major job. To his son's dismay, 'The Lock' refuses to commit the job he was broken out of jail to do, his years in prison having given him strong food for thought about the hopelessness of the criminal life.

title: When I'm Sixty Four
description: Yarra Central police are confronted with what seems to be an impossible crime to solve. A fortress-like factory guarded by dogs and security fences is broken into and industrial secrets worth thousands of dollars are stolen from under the guards noses.

title: The Best We Know
description: Lorna Matthews, a spokeswoman for woman's rights and social reforms, is threatened with a charge of drunk driving and accuses Sen. Det. Peters of accepting a bribe from her. She decides to enlist the help of an influential friend.

title: Standover
description: An old friend of Det. Peters is about to be married, but his girlfriend has a criminal background that is exploited by operatives of a stand over racket.

title: Don't Ask Me
description: Const. Dwyer is first on the scene of a narcotics robbery at a warehouse, and is seriously bashed when he attempts to apprehend the criminals. One of the drug pushers is trained in unarmed combat, and he controls the supply for 17 - year- old addict Liz Green, a sad and dominated character from a good family who is controlled, degraded and nearly destroyed.

title: Willie
description: Willie Evans is released from prison after serving three years for the theft of $17,000 which was not recovered on his arrest. He attracts great interest from his wife, his brother, a fellow former convict and the police.

title: My Pretty Maid
description: When a neighbor of Det. Sgt. Vickers becomes involved with a gang of hoodlums, it causes great concern for the Yarra Central police, particularly Policewoman Stewart who becomes a victim of the thugs.

title: Damsel in Distress
description: A young girl makes a complaint to the police to prevent her father from re-marrying. When this doesn't work, she employs an inept criminal to use more drastic action.

title: Bella
description: Yarra Central police have a baffling case on their hands when a prostitute befriends a young criminal. This association, together with the arrival of the prostitute's runaway daughter, leads to a tragic end.

title: Young Hennessy
description: Young Hennessy, a boxing champion of the 1930's, is reputed to have hidden away a great deal of money in his old house. Knowing that so many people are trying to take advantage of the old man a young boy, Luke, decides to manage his life.

title: The Criminal Type
description: Banner's girlfriend Jenny Franklin provides support when Banner is forced to investigate the possible criminal past of a couple of old friends that Banner has known for years.

title: Fear Street
description: Yarra Central police are called in ti find the sender of anonymous obscene letters to a number of married women all living in the same street.

title: You Do Your Best
description: When an attractive but intellectual disabled girl is almost raped by a couple of thugs, her father takes the law into his own hands to punish those responsible.

title: For Old Crimes Sake
description: An old man's dreams for his beloved grandniece results in tragedy when he turns to crime to help her establish a decent life.

title: Hit Run
description: Yarra Central police are set a difficult task when a young girl is killed following a hit and run accident.

title: Triangle
description: A policeman is critically injured when struck by the getaway car from an armed robbery, and Det. Sgt. Banner finds his personal life in turmoil when an x-boyfriend of Jenny's arrives from London on business.

title: Backlash
description: Mal White has served eight years for robbery with violence and attempted bribery. All he wants on his release is a savage revenge on those whom he perceives to have done him wrong. One of his intended victims is Sgt. Scotty Macleod.

title: Talk Back
description: Billy Miller, a 10-year-old boy, goes missing. His disappearance went unnoticed by his mother, and Yarra Central police search for his body in a creek at the tip, and fear that a man with a known record of sex offenses is involved.

title: In at the Kill
description: When an itinerant, middle-aged bushman arrives in Melbourne, he soon finds himself involved in a turmoil of trouble. The situation is complicated further when he appears to fall in love with policewoman Margaret Stewart.

title: The Slasher
description: An ex-policeman investigates attacks on girls by a mentally deranged razor slasher. The further the investigation proceeds, the More it points to his own son being the culprit.

title: Sergeant Banner
description: A Gang of Four dangerous criminals pull a major payroll robbery, and the entire Yarra Central crew is called in to assist. While arresting one of the thieves, Banner is shot in the shoulder and is forced to take a Fiew days leave. He spends the time with his girlfriend Jenny, but her constant contact with friends she new in England plus the pressure of Banner's job puts a strain on their relationship. So much so that Banner fears he may loose her. With this problem on his mind, plus the efforts to locate and capture the ringleader of the gang, he comes to the point where he almost has to choose between the police force and Jenny.

title: Charity Affair
description: Police protection is requested at a charity function where a routine job turns into a possible murder investigation. Const. Dwyer takes on an undercover role posing as a criminal.

title: The Munich Job
description: Yarra Central police become involved in an Interpol inquiry when it is thought that a suspect for a recent jewel robbery in Munich. May be living in the area.

title: Approach with Caution
description: Police are on full alert when they are informed that a sadistic psychopath and a mad bomber, who have both escaped from a country hospital, are heading towards Melbourne in an attempt to destroy those who helped imprisoned them.

title: Emporer Craig
description: Matthew Craig, the powerful head of a large publishing company, becomes the target for a series of bitter hoaxes. Investigations reveal that Craig has many enemies.

title: An Eye for an Eye
description: Det. Sgt. Vickers finds his career is in jeopardy after a police chase, when he faces a charge for the manslaughter of the son of a prominent barrister.

title: For My Next Trick
description: The presence of a brilliant pick-pocket is felt when racing carnival punters complain of missing wallets. Police spend many hours to race meetings to track down the offender

title: All for One
description: An unmotivated bashing looks like it could be the beginning of a series of similar loutish crimes. Suspicion falls on the son of a wealthy self-made man, who uses money to buy affection and obedience from his children, and is forced to face the fact that the making of money is not the answer to all human problems. Const. Kevin Dwyer has applied for CIB work and has been accepted for detective training, which will require his transferring away from Yarra Central.

title: The Battle of Waterloo Street
description: A developer uses unscrupulous methods to force people to sell their homes in Waterloo Street to make way for a shopping complex. Miss Bobby Paigely has been living in her house for 30 years and refuses to move. Her boarders and friends come to her aid, and decide on a campaign against the development company which result in a street battle, complete with flour bombs and squirting water hoses. The Yarra Central police arrive and become embroiled in the fight.

title: Friends and Neighbours
description: When a young boy is killed in a road accident, Yarra Central police suspect an ulterior motive for his death after they learn of threats against his family.

title: Parable
description: Yarra Central Police question the activities of a young evangelist when it appears that he has assaulted a young prostitute.

title: Mad About the Boy
description: Jill Ferris, an old school friend of Margaret Stewart, finds herself in trouble through her lover for a younger man, which leads into crime.

title: Baxter's Son
description: Yarra Central is rocked by a wave of housebreaking's, all having a common link. Vickers becomes personally involved when a high ranking detective and a friend emerge as prime suspects.

title: The Tribunal
description: Yarra Central police find themselves involved in a struggle between political factions when they investigate an attempted assassination by a foreign agent.

title: Nobody Cares
description: A schoolgirl is bashed unconscious, and another disappears. The police suspect rape and kidnap, but new evidence shows the crimes in a different light, and revealed a new facet of the two girls character.

title: The Man in the Saville Row Suit
description: Yarra Central police are up against formidable odds when they track down the mastermind of a daring daylight robbery.

title: The Senator's Wife
description: A senator's wife appears to have been robbed, however the lack of any physical evidence cause police to suspect that she may be delusional.

title: Maria
description: The new constable at Yarra Central, Roger Wilson, finds himself the victim of an old man's obstinacy, and eventually puts himself in danger to rescue Banner from possible injury.

title: Jo
description: While trying to escape, a housebreaker is struck by Det. Peters driving the C.I. car, and is seriously injured. During the subsequent investigation, police delve into the past of the housebreaker'a girlfriend.

title: Goodbye Charlie
description: New Constable Bob Parry is giving the Yarra Central police moments of anxiety; car thieves are complicating inquiries; Policewoman Margaret Stewart has a secret; and Det. Peters involves himself in a doubtful romance.

title: None So Blind
description: Detectives deal with a baffling case of robbery with violence committed on a young woman who then disappears. Policewoman Margaret Stewart leaves the police force to get married.

title: Cleanliness Is Next to Godliness
description: A special detective is assigned to Yarra Central to investigate cases of missing females. One particular case reveals that a masked assailant is at large - with a terrible and horrible result. Ray Preston receives his promotion to Senior Constable.

title: The Professionals
description: A bungling criminal finds himself involved with big-time activities and causes the police of Yarra Central some anxious moments when he mistakenly steals some highly explosive chemicals.

title: Open Season
description: Yarra Central police have a difficult task ahead of them as they search for a prisoner taken from them at gunpoint. Then they learn that the person who freed the prisoner is out to get them - and in particular Det. Sgt. Banner.

title: Now Be a Good Boy
description: Two elusive confidence tricksters, just two of an entire family of criminals, have Yarra Central police working around the clock trying to collate enough evidence to apprehend them.

title: Rag Doll
description: Two police recruits are accused of instigating a fight with a gang of youths. A controversy erupts concerning the training of police recruits when one of the youths suffers permanent brain damage as a result.

title: A Cry in the Dark
description: Constable Wilson is accused of assault during the arrest of a wanted man. Det. Sgt. Banner, while interviewing eyewitnesses, discoverers a case of child bashing.

title: We've Made It, We're Rich
description: Yarra Central police search for a vicious criminal and his hostage after a bank robbery. Unknown to them, another criminal joins in the search for an entirely different reason.

title: The Vigil
description: A policewoman temporarily stationed at Yarra Central becomes the target of a seemingly maniacal killer. Police desperately try to establish the killer's identity and motive before the threat can be carried out.

title: Eye Witness
description: A girl is criminally assaulted, and is so shocked she can't remember who did it. Two youths are suspected until police learn of another witness.

title: Hello Stranger
description: When a young woman is released from Greenleigh woman's Prison she faces many problems. Policewomen Jane Bell, assigned from Russell St to Yarra Central, tries to help her but soon learns that personal involvement is not always the answer.

title: A Touch of Art
description: While investigating a series of art thefts, Yarra Central police receive unusual help from a housewife who is frustrated by her estranged husband's sense of revenge.

title: The Driver's All Mine
description: When an ambulance with a police escort and another vehicle are involved in a collision, there eventuates a major mystery for the Yarra Central Police.

title: A Cry of Wolf
description: Yarra Central police are dubious when a derelict reports a murder. Their doubts appear justified when there is no evidence of a crime, but the derro is then found to be the next victim.

title: The Last of the 78's
description: Yarra Central is the victim of an idealistic practical joker, Jonathon Gramophone, who helps a quiet little man, Harold Sloane, get even with a used car dealer who cheated him.

title: The Woman from Poland
description: Police are concerned about a polish immigrant who lives in Yarra Central, isolated from the outside by her memories. When a boarder moves in with her, it appearers that the grim past she left behind in Poland has caught up with her.

title: Why Can't He Leave Me Alone?
description: A young stripper, fearing for her own safety, refuses to help the police when her escapee ex-boyfriend goes on a revenge campaign against an old enemy.

title: Lonely Hearts
description: The assault on a spinster turns police attention to a marriage bureau and escort service which they suspect May be covering up a prostitution racket.

title: Fair Cop
description: Yarra Central police investigate a gangland execution and become concerned when a crime-hating colleague intimidates a suspect. Det. Peters find himself totally opposed to the other policeman's attitude to criminals.

title: Billy's Choice
description: When two men help a prisoner in his escape, the police suspect the motive is not the prisoner's freedom, but to help them pull off a bigger crime.

title: Middle Man
description: A former criminal finds going straight very tough when other criminals pressure him to for help to do more crimes.

title: A Man of Substance
description: A businessman is assaulted and robbed, and the police find his confusion over the incident very puzzling, when they check his company's background and find things not quite as they should be.

title: Was Calling Him Bogey, I
description: Yarra Central police investigate a house breaking and capture the burglar, but unbeknown to them he isn't the only person in the house. The occupant of the house, a young girl, spends a day of terror until the police finally realize the situation.

title: Dying Deposition
description: Two attempts on the life of a youth and the subsequent murder of his girlfriend force Sgt. Vickers into visiting Beechworth Prison in an attempt to get some information from one of the inmates.

title: Easy Mark
description: Police have problems with an angry husband who is attempting to find his wife - the only person who knows the truth about a brutal attack on a teenage girl.

title: Sat'dee Avro
description: Constable Wilson, experiencing a typical Saturday afternoon in Yarra Central, when he accidentally uncovers a plot to blow up a warehouse.

title: Time Payment
description: A man's car is blown up and his wife threatened. Yarra Central police are mystified as to the reason until they find out the victim has a shady past and someone is out for revenge.

title: Shadows
description: An unstable girl is the victim of a terror campaign, little suspecting that the one person she trusts is behind it. Investigations lead to doubts about her mental health, however Const. Paul Gray, newly arrived at Yarra Central, proves his worth as a cop when he helps solve the crime.

title: The Lame Ducks
description: Police are outsmarted by the extreme efficiency of a spate of robberies, until an ex-parole officer who has been recruiting an army of criminals emerges as the brains behind the scenes, recruiting an army of crims to pull the big jobs.

title: Unfit to Plead
description: A dating service comes under scrutiny when police realize that file cards on lonely female applicants have been stolen by a mentally unstable man. The mind of the man finally cracks under pressure.

title: A Couple of Mates
description: An elderly man befriends a youth when he sees him escaping from the scene of a hold up. A strong relationship builds up between them, leading to the old man endangering his life.

title: Every Sheila's Dream
description: Three youths abduct a young girl. She finds unexpected help from one of the captors when the most dangerous of the three decide to attack her.

title: Nicky
description: The brother of a mentally challenged youth causes suffering and trouble to his father and almost causes his father to commit a serious crime.

title: What Will My Friends Say?
description: The daughter of an upper-class family, Sarah Carr, is found raped an a golf course. Yarra Central police become suspicious of her brother David, realizing he may be the cause of the crime by 'setting up' Sarah to be raped by his mates.

title: A Bird in the Hand
description: A factory manager is outraged when two bogus policemen steal a payroll from one of his staff. Policewoman Kim Baker works undercover as an employee when Yarra Central police suspect it could be an inside job.

title: Two Hours of Madness
description: Det. Sgt. Banner poses as the father of a kidnap victim. However, the situation becomes dangerous when the kidnappers discover his true identity.

title: A Sense of Duty: Part 1
description: Det. Sgt. Banner finds himself facing a murder charge after shooting a man he has been trying to put behind bars for several years.

title: A Sense of Duty: Part 2
description: Det. Sgt. Banner faces a coroner's inquiry, and indications are that he will leave the force. Banner is torn between his dedication to his police duties, and his love for his girlfriend Jenny who has recently contacted him from London.

title: No Prize for Second
description: A terror campaign is waged against a young woman, and police suspect a highly regarded and influential councilor is responsible.

title: The Fanatic
description: A Polish widower and his daughter fall victim to a campaign of harassment instigated by a highly prejudiced man.

title: The Vickers Way
description: Vickers has the Yarra Central police intrigued as he works his way through a case using his own methods, with none of the other police knowing exactly why they are doing as he orders.

title: Take No for an Answer
description: The subject of rape is investigated by the Yarra Central police, not only as police but also human beings. Policewoman Jane Bell is one of the major instigators of the discussions that take place, and the arguments that follow.

title: The World Belongs to the Young
description: A timber yard employee, unable to cope with modern day changes and domestic problems, suffers a nervous breakdown - with tragic consequences.

title: A Civil Question
description: Yarra Central police have a hard time when a middle-aged couple make constant exaggerated complaints against a neighbour and her mentally challenged son.

title: The Daughters of Man
description: While investigating a series of unusual thefts from the local library, Yarra Central police uncover an equally unusual religious sect.

title: The Human Factor
description: An explosion in the computer room of a car accessories firm leads to the downfall of a man who suffers from being redundant.

title: Life's a Gamble
description: An ineffectual man who is a compulsive gambler unknowingly gambles on his life when he becomes in gangland warfare.

title: Something to Live Up To
description: An ex-detective and close friend of Det. Sgt. Banner lies to protect his son after discovering his involvement in a robbery.

title: Little Raver
description: The parents of psychopathic teenager Wendy Sherlock have difficulty proving their innocence when it appears to the police that they are mistreating her. When a young man is badly slashed with a razor blade, the girl's parents suspect her - but she appears so innocent on the surface and displays such a plausible mien that even doctors and the police are fooled.

title: Big Fish, Small Fry
description: An assault on an accountant has the Yarra Central police baffled until they discover that the take over of a major prostitution racket is behind the assault.

title: Just for Kicks
description: Constable Gray's relationship with his girlfriend is strained when he is faced with having to arrest her brother.

title: Tell Me Your Troubles My Friend
description: A businessman has been under intense strain since the disappearance of his partner- and the Yarra Central police gradually unravel a murder case. Const. Wilson receives a transfer to Mansfield.

title: When Pride Takes Precedence
description: Yarra Central police investigate when the wife of a prominent and self-centered councilor receives a blackmail threat regarding her illegitimate son.

title: Rubber Bunny
description: A man is released from prison while serving a sentence for a crime he did not commit. He turns to Sgt. Banner for help, who was partly the cause of his conviction.

title: Check, Check, Check
description: Police investigate the disappearance of a teenage wife and an outraged husband with a gun.

title: Once Upon a Time
description: Three young men, on three consecutive days, hold up the Apex Finance Company to raise some cash to marry Daisy King, daughter of a wealthy racing magnate.

title: Dead Fall
description: Det. Sgt. Banner spends six grueling hours on the roof of a high building trying to prevent a young girl from committing suicide.

title: Friends, 'Who Needs 'Em?'
description: Det. Peters is disillusioned when a close friendship is threatened, particularly when, as both a policeman and a friend, he is simply trying to help.

title: Horrie and Charlie
description: Two totally hopeless would-be criminals have the Yarra Central police running around in circles to the extreme annoyance of Det. Sgt. Vickers.

title: 1956 and All That
description: Two aging rockers confronted with a young female prison escapee find themselves not so tough as the imagined that they were.

title: Agnes Triumphant
description: Agnes, a pathetic but happy alcoholic, meets another alcoholic, Fred, who asks her to marry him. Fred has a long history of violent crime, and Agnes learns that the only reason he wants to marry her is because her sister Beryl owns a wine bar, and he thinks it is a good way to ensure a lifetime supply of free grog.

title: His Word Against Mine
description: A highly respected Yarra Central councilor is suspected of being involved in homosexual activities, but a youth who is involved gives police another version of the situation. Det. Sgt. Banner plans to marry his girlfriend Jenny Franklin, and resigns from the police force to take an extended honeymoon and to find a 'more suitable' profession.

title: Today Ends at Dawn
description: Sen. Det. Tom Morgan transfers to Yarra Central, and his Horst case is that of a missing paper boy who is found dead, the apparent victim of a hit and run accident. Investigations lead the Yarra Central police to a nearby factory.
